User Stories
Epic 1: Ensemble Machine Learning Detection Engine
US-001: Advanced Malware Detection with Ensemble Methods
As a Security Engineer
I want an ensemble ML engine that combines Random Forest, XGBoost, and LGBM algorithms
So that I can achieve 99.4% accuracy in malware detection with explainable AI insights

Acceptance Criteria:
- Ensemble weights: 40% Random Forest, 35% XGBoost, 25% LGBM
- Real-time inference with <100ms latency per package
- SHAP explanations for all predictions
- Confidence scores with threshold configuration
- False positive rate <2%
US-002: Zero-Day Malware Detection
As a DevOps Engineer
I want XGBoost-based zero-day detection capabilities
So that I can identify previously unknown malicious packages in our CI/CD pipeline

Acceptance Criteria:
- 98% accuracy for zero-day threats
- Feature engineering with PE header analysis
- TF-IDF vectorization for signature analysis
- Real-time model updates every 4 hours
- Integration with threat intelligence feeds
US-003: Behavioral Analytics Engine
As a Security Analyst
I want real-time behavioral analysis using UEBA and Graph Neural Networks
So that I can detect sophisticated supply chain attacks through anomalous behavior patterns

Acceptance Criteria:
- 92.7% fraud detection accuracy
- Microsecond-level event processing with Apache Flink
- 68% latency reduction compared to batch processing
- Graph-based relationship analysis
- Behavioral baseline establishment
Epic 2: Advanced Dependency Analysis
US-004: Cross-Language Dependency Analysis
As a Full-Stack Developer
I want comprehensive dependency analysis across Go, Python, and JavaScript ecosystems
So that I can identify phantom dependencies and cross-language vulnerabilities

Acceptance Criteria:
- Support for Go modules, Python requirements, npm packages
- Phantom dependency detection (0-60% of dependencies)
- Transitive dependency tree visualization
- Language-specific attack vector identification
- Integration with 12 Go-specific attack vectors from GoSurf
US-005: Graph-Based Dependency Mapping
As a Security Architect
I want transformer-based graph analysis for dependency relationships
So that I can detect subtle supply chain compromises across complex dependency trees

Acceptance Criteria:
- Neo4j integration for dependency storage
- Transformer algorithms for long-range dependency analysis
- Real-time graph updates on package changes
- Vulnerability propagation analysis
- Supply chain risk scoring
Epic 3: Runtime Security Monitoring
US-006: eBPF-Based Runtime Monitoring
As a Platform Engineer
I want eBPF-powered runtime behavior analysis
So that I can monitor package behavior in production with minimal performance overhead

Acceptance Criteria:
- In-kernel execution monitoring
- Process-level forensics and telemetry
- Container workload analysis
- <2% CPU overhead for monitoring
- Real-time threat correlation
US-007: Container Runtime Security
As a Kubernetes Operator
I want Kubernetes-native security with ML-powered behavioral baselines
So that I can detect runtime deviations and respond automatically

Acceptance Criteria:
- Kubernetes admission controller integration
- RASP (Runtime Application Self-Protection) capabilities
- Automatic baseline establishment
- Policy enforcement automation
- Integration with existing K8s security tools
Epic 4: Advanced SBOM Management
US-008: AI-Enhanced SBOM Analysis
As a Compliance Officer
I want AI-enhanced SBOM generation and analysis
So that I can maintain accurate software inventories with real-time vulnerability correlation

Acceptance Criteria:
- Multi-tool SBOM generation (Syft, Trivy, Grype)
- ML-powered quality assessment
- Real-time vulnerability correlation with NVD, OSV, GitHub Advisories
- CycloneDX and SPDX format support
- Automated compliance reporting
US-009: Dynamic SBOM Evolution Tracking
As a Release Manager
I want time-series tracking of SBOM changes
So that I can understand supply chain evolution and impact assessment

Acceptance Criteria:
- Delta analysis between SBOM versions
- Component lifecycle tracking
- Risk trend analysis
- Automated change notifications
- Integration with CI/CD pipelines
Epic 5: Cryptographic Verification and Future-Proofing
US-010: Post-Quantum Cryptography Preparation
As a Security Architect
I want quantum-safe cryptographic verification implementation
So that our supply chain security remains protected against future quantum threats

Acceptance Criteria:
- NIST-approved post-quantum algorithms (ML-DSA, ML-KEM, SLH-DSA)
- Hybrid cryptography approach (classical + post-quantum)
- Migration pathway for existing signatures
- Key rotation automation
- Performance benchmarking
US-011: Zero-Knowledge Proof Verification
As a Supply Chain Security Engineer
I want ZK-proof based package verification using STARKs
So that I can verify package integrity without revealing sensitive information

Acceptance Criteria:
- STARK-based verification system
- No trusted setup requirements
- Integration with existing signing infrastructure
- Transparent audit logs
- Scalable proof generation
Epic 6: Threat Intelligence and Risk Assessment
US-012: Real-Time Threat Intelligence Correlation
As a Threat Intelligence Analyst
I want real-time correlation of multiple threat intelligence feeds
So that I can identify emerging threats and update detection models automatically

Acceptance Criteria:
- Integration with 5+ threat intelligence sources
- Event-driven architecture with Kafka Streams
- Automated model retraining
- Threat landscape visualization
- Custom threat feed integration
US-013: Game Theory-Based Risk Assessment
As a Risk Manager
I want mathematical risk assessment using game theory models
So that I can optimize security investment decisions and supplier relationships

Acceptance Criteria:
- Nash equilibrium calculations for security investments
- Supplier risk scoring using game theory
- Progressive penalty systems for malicious actors
- ROI optimization for security controls
- Integration with business metrics